ited Kingdom, Wales enjoys independent representation in major world ___ing events such as the FIFA World Cup and in the Rugby World Cup, but competes as part of the England cricket team and as Great Britain in some other competitions, including the Olympics.","wiki"),("prose","5","___ is a form or technique of language that exhibits a natural flow of speech and grammatical structure. Novels, textbooks and newspaper articles are all examples of ___. The word ___ is frequently used in opposition to traditional poetry, which is language with a regular structure and a common unit of verse based on metre or rhyme. However, as T. S. Eliot noted, whereas 'the distinction between verse and ___ is clear, the distinction between poetry and ___ is obscure'; developments in modern literature, including free verse and ___ poetry, have led to the two techniques indicating two ends on a spectrum of ways to compose language, as opposed to two discrete options.","wiki"),("steps","5","Dance moves or dance ___  are usually isolated, defined, and organized so that beginning dancers can learn and use them independently of each other. However, more complex movements are influenced by musicality and lyrical relevance to express emotions or refer to a message. Dance moves tend to emphasize the concepts of lead and follow and connection.","wiki"),("flags","5","This is a list of ___ used exclusively in Wales.","wiki"),("mixed","5","A ___ language is a language that arises among a bilingual group combining aspects of two or more languages but not clearly deriving primarily from any single language. It differs from a creole or pidgin language in that, whereas creoles/pidgins arise from populations trying to imitate a language in which they have no fluency, a ___ language arises in a population that is fluent in both of the source languages.","wiki"),("inner","5","The ___ Hebrides .","wiki"),("towns","5","The cultural importance placed on charters remains, and it is not an unusual event for __